        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Spirits of creatures that died within the lantern’s light haunt it. While the lantern is open, these spirits surround the spirit lamp, slowing and attacking all creatures within the lantern’s light. A creature that starts its turn within 30 feet of the spirit lamp has its speed halved and must make a DC 15 Wisdom saving throw, taking 10 (3d6) necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If the spirit lamp dies and the lantern is open, the lantern’s spirits continue to harm creatures within 30 feet of it until the lantern is destroyed or closed.",
